    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <head>No. 119.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Martinez</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Chili in the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-10-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 27, 1881</date>. (Received November
                                1.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 28.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the pleasure to inform your
                            excellency that the treaty for the settlement of the boundary question,
                            concluded between Chili and the Argentine Republic, having been approved
                            by the Congresses of both nations, has been ratified, and that the
                            ratifications have been exchanged.</p>
                <p>As very valuable services were lent in the conclusion of that treaty by
                            the honorable ministers of the United States at Santiago and Buenos
                            Ayres, my government through me, performs the pleasing duty of returning
                            its warmest thanks to your excellency, as it has already done personally
                            to the distinguished diplomatist Thomas H. [meaning A.] Osborn.</p>
                <p>With sentiments, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M. MARTINEZ.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
